net.antidot.api.upload
Class Connector

java.lang.Object
  net.antidot.api.upload.Connector

public class Connector
extends java.lang.Object

PaF upload connector.

This connector allows upload of one or more files to specific PaF through Antidot Back Office.

Constructor Detail

Connector

public Connector(java.lang.String host,
                 Service service,
                 java.lang.String pafName,
                 Authentication authentication)
Constructs new PaF connector.

Connector is created with default URL scheme AFS_SCHEME_HTTP (see Scheme).

Parameters:
host - [in] host name of the server hosting Antidot Back Office.
service - [in] service to consider on the hosting server (see Service).
pafName - [in] name of the PaF for the specified service.
authentication - [in] authentication method along with user name and password.

Connector

public Connector(Scheme scheme,
                 java.lang.String host,
                 Service service,
                 java.lang.String pafName,
                 Authentication authentication)
Constructs new PaF connector.

Parameters:
scheme - [in] specific scheme to use for the connection (see Scheme).
host - [in] host name of the server hosting Antidot Back Office.
service - [in] service to consider on the hosting server (see Service).
pafName - [in] name of the PaF for the specified service.
authentication - [in] authentication method along with user name and password.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when required scheme is not supported by the connector.
